# Line Endings

- Preserve the existing line-ending style of every file you edit.
- In this repository on Windows, prefer `CRLF` for new text files unless nearby files or explicit repo configuration require a different style.
- Avoid introducing line-ending-only diffs unless the user explicitly asks for normalization.
- If a file already uses a consistent EOL style, keep that style unchanged after edits.
